### 🟠 High

<br>

[HIGH] File: `optimcore/src/lib.rs`:563 – Coordinate descent is missing active set optimization, severely impacting performance.
→ **Issue**: The coordinate descent algorithm iterates over every single feature (`for j in 0..n_vars`) in every outer loop. For sparse models like Lasso, where many coefficients become zero, this is extremely inefficient. Competing libraries like `glmnet` use "active set" optimization to only iterate over features with non-zero coefficients, leading to speedups of 10-100x.
→ **Fix**: Implement an active set strategy. Maintain a list of indices of non-zero coefficients (the "active set"). In the main loop, only iterate over this set. Periodically (e.g., every 5-10 iterations), iterate over all features to check for any that violate the Karush-Kuhn-Tucker (KKT) conditions and add them to the active set if they do.

```rust
